data.chText: 环境；背景
data.enText: a set of surroundings; the place at which sth happens

data.chText: 乡村、理想、优美、田园等的环境
data.enText: a rural/an ideal/a beautiful/an idyllic, etc. setting

data.chText: 环境气氛无可挑剔，正是一个美好的圣诞节所需要的。
data.enText: It was the perfect setting for a wonderful Christmas.

data.chText: （戏剧、小说等的）情节背景
data.enText: the place and time at which the action of a play, novel, etc. takes place

data.chText: 以当代生活为背景的短篇小说
data.enText: short stories with a contemporary setting

data.chText: （机器上调节速度、高度、温度等的）挡，级，点
data.enText: a position at which the controls on a machine can be set, to set the speed, height, temperature, etc.

data.chText: 对引擎的性能在不同的挡上做了试验。
data.enText: The performance of the engine was tested at different settings.

data.chText: （为诗等谱的）曲
data.enText: music written to go with a poem, etc.

data.chText: 舒伯特为歌德的一首诗谱的曲
data.enText: Schubert's setting of a poem by Goethe

data.chText: （镶嵌宝石的）底座，底板，托板
data.enText: a piece of metal in which a precious stone is fixed to form a piece of jewellery

data.chText: （摆在桌上供一人用的）一套餐具
data.enText: a complete set of equipment for eating with (knife, fork, spoon, glass, etc.) for one person, arranged on a table

data.chText: 一个座位的整套餐具
data.enText: a place setting

data.text: environment ♦ setting ♦ surroundings ♦ background ♦ backdrop ♦ situation

data.chText: 以上各词均指人或事物生存或所处的环境。
data.enText: These are all words for the type of place in which sb/sth exists or is situated.
environment

data.chText: 指影响人或事物的行为或发展的环境：
data.enText: the conditions in a place that affect the behaviour and development of sb/sth

data.chText: 不幸的家庭环境可能对孩子的行为造成影响。
data.enText: An unhappy home environment can affect children's behaviour.

data.chText: 令人愉快的工作环境
data.enText: a pleasant working environment
setting

data.chText: 指事情发生或所处的环境、背景：
data.enText: a place or situation of a particular type, in which sth happens or exists

data.chText: 这岛为音乐会提供了优美的田园布景。
data.enText: The island provided an idyllic setting for the concert.
surroundings

data.chText: 指周围的环境：
data.enText: everything that is around or near sb/sth

data.chText: 这些棚屋与周围的环境浑然一体，非常和谐。
data.enText: The huts blend in perfectly with their surroundings.
background

data.chText: 指对主体事物起衬托作用的景物、背景：
data.enText: the things or area that are/is behind or around the main objects or people that are in a place or picture

data.chText: 远处的山峦白雪覆盖。
data.enText: The mountains in the background were capped with snow.
backdrop

data.chText: 指事情发生的环境或对主体事物起衬托作用的背景：
data.enText: ( formal ) the scenery surrounding an event; the things or area behind the main objects in a place

data.chText: 活动在雄伟的阿特拉斯山脉举行。
data.enText: The events took place against the dramatic backdrop of the Atlas mountains.
situation

data.chText: 指城镇或建筑物的地理位置、环境特点：
data.enText: ( rather formal ) the type of area or surroundings that a town or building has

data.chText: 小城坐落在宽阔而草木苍翠的山谷中，环境优美。
data.enText: The town is in a beautiful situation in a wide green valley.
in (a/an) environment/setting/surroundings/situation
against a/the background/backdrop (of sth)
a (good, etc.) environment/setting/situation for sth
(a/an) new/unfamiliar environment/setting/surroundings
sb/sth's immediate environment/setting/surroundings
(a) dramatic setting/surroundings/background/backdrop

means: (机器上调节速度、高度、温度等的)挡，级，点

ex.chText: 我们的故事发生在古罗马。
ex.enText: Our story has its setting in ancient Rome.

ex.chText: 该导演把20世纪30年代作为这部电视剧的故事背景。
ex.enText: The 1930s was used by the director as the setting for this television series.

ex.chText: 该岛是海滨度假的绝佳地方。
ex.enText: The island is the perfect setting for a beach holiday.

synonyms.bx: 指戏剧、小说、电影等中情节发生的背景，包括人物活动的时间、地点和条件，也可指某处的环境。

ex.chText: 在背景中可以看到安第斯山脉。
ex.enText: In the background you can see the Andean mountain range.

ex.chText: 你了解那个人的家庭背景吗？
ex.enText: Do you know that fellow's family background?

ex.chText: 该校学生具有不同的种族背景。
ex.enText: The school has pupils from different ethnic backgrounds.

ex.chText: 他不了解这案件的背景情况，所以无法评论。
ex.enText: He couldn't comment without knowing the background of the case.

synonyms.bx: 指舞台或图片的背景，现尤指某人或某事物的背景情况。

tr: arrangement of scenery and properties to represent the place where a play or movie is enacted
a mounting consisting of a piece of metal (as in a ring or other jewelry) that holds a gem in place
example: the diamond was in a plain gold mount

tr: a table service for one person
example: a place setting of sterling flatware

tr: the context and environment in which something is set
example: the perfect setting for a ghost story
he changed the setting on the thermostat

tr: the set of facts or circumstances that surround a situation or event
the state of the environment in which a situation exists
example: you can't do that in a university setting

value.def: A particular setting is a particular place or type of surroundings where something is or takes place.

example.ex: Rome is the perfect setting for romance...
example.tran: 罗马是最适合谈情说爱的地方。

example.ex: Perth was the setting for the SNP's conference this year...
example.tran: 珀斯是今年苏格兰国民党大会的召开地。

example.ex: The house is in a lovely setting in the Malvern hills.
example.tran: 房子坐落在莫尔文丘陵地区，周围景色迷人。

gramarinfo.label: usu with supp, oft N <l>for</l> n

value.def: A setting is one of the positions to which the controls of a device such as a cooker, stove, or heater can be adjusted.

example.ex: You can boil the fish fillets on a high setting.
example.tran: 可以用高火煮无骨鱼片。

value.tran: (炉具、热水器等上可供调节的)挡，级，点，刻度

value.def: A table setting is the complete set of equipment that one person needs to eat a meal, including knives, forks, spoons, and glasses.
